               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="INS0174MAKM"></placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1933" notAfter="1934">According to <ref target="#coloph1"/>, the manuscript was completed in 
                        <date calendar="ethiopian" when-custom="1926"  notBefore="1933" notAfter="1934"> 1926 A.M (= 1933/34 A.D.)</date>
                       </origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>According to <ref target="#coloph1"/>, the manuscript was donated to <placeName ref="INS0174MAKM"/> 
                     by <persName role="donor" ref="PRS15465Gazzachen"><roleName type="title">Wayzaro</roleName> Gazzāččǝn Gabra Ḥǝywat</persName> 
                     (her father’s name is provided in <ref target="#d10"/>). She was likely connected with the family of <persName ref="PRS5227haylase"><roleName type="rank">Rās</roleName> Ḫayla Śǝllāse Gugsā</persName>.
                     Her baptismal name, Walatta Māryām, appears in many supplication formulas, e.g. on <locus target="#3ra #4vc #14rc #58vb"/>.
                   
                   The late Emperor <persName ref="PRS10378Yohanne"/> and his “children” (most likely not all of them were his biological children): <persName ref="PRS2012Arayas">ʾArʾayā Śǝllāse</persName>, 
                     <persName ref="PRS15469WaldaGiyorgis"></persName>, <persName ref="PRS15468HaylaSellase">Ḫāyla Śǝllāse</persName> and <persName ref="PRS15470SegeMaryam"></persName> 
                     appear in a supplication formula on <locus target="#55vc"/>. Their names also appear 
                     in other supplication formulas throughout the manuscript:
                     <persName ref="PRS15469WaldaGiyorgis"/> <locus target="#25rc #73va"/>; <persName ref="PRS15470SegeMaryam"/> <locus target="#51rb #83rc"/>;
                     <persName ref="PRS15468HaylaSellase">Ḫāyla Śǝllāse</persName><locus target="#64ra #81rc"/>; 
                     <persName ref="PRS15471WalattaKirosG">Walatta Kiros</persName> <locus target="#67rc #76rb"/>.
                     A number of other people associated with her family appear in the legends of the miniatures.
                    </provenance>
               </history>
